    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-02-27T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-02-27T07:00:00-05:00" n="29"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d29">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a3/716: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-27T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 27, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 27—8:06
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>91. The informal conversations with the Japanese were resumed by a conversation
                    between Senator Reed and Ambassador Matsudaira<note n="47" xml:id="d29fn47"
                        >Japanese Ambassador in Great Britain and member of the Japanese
                        delegation.</note> after a luncheon at the Japanese Embassy on Tuesday. A
                    possible scheme of compromise on figures was worked out by the two of them
                    together but as yet this delegation and as far as we know the Japanese
                    delegation have not accepted these figures. Thus any possible figures which
                    might appear in Tokyo either in press leaks or otherwise lack any official
                    approval and are completely unofficial. When any definite progress has been made
                    you will be informed.</p>
                <p>Please repeat to Tokyo.<note n="47a" xml:id="d29fn47a">Transmitted to the Embassy
                        in Japan as Department’s telegram No. 38, February 27, 10 a.m.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
